				 Suspensions revoked
																								Lucknow, Nov. 24 (PTI): The Uttar Pradesh government today revoked the suspension of 22 senior IPS officers in a police recruitment scam, but removed from a key post a senior official who headed the investigation.																								Less than two months after suspending 25 officers for alleged irregularities in the recruitment of Provincial Armed Constabulary and police constables during the rule of Mulayam Singh Yadav, the state government lifted the action against 22 of them. 																								A decision on the remaining three could not be taken as they were yet to respond to their showcause notices.																								On the other hand, the post of additional director-general of police of the special task force, held by Shailaja Kant Mishra, who had headed the committee probing the scam, was abolished today, the chief ministers principal secretary Shailesh Krishna said.																								Krishna said the STF job would now be looked after by the additional director-general, law and order, Brij Lal. 
